Description: Forcing functions are used in place of ordinary differential
    equation (ODE) state variables whenever an equation governing the state
    variable is unknown.  Instead, the equation is replaced with another
    function that depends only on time instead of any other state variables in
    the system of ODEs.  Using ODEs is less common in domain-specific
    programming languages like Stan, therefore this package primarily provides
    a vignette explaining how to use ODEs in Stan.
